# Server

- lightweight
- SvelteKit as full-stack framework (API routes + SSR).
- MVP: in-memory data store (single Node process, seeded on first read).
- Later: scalable via Kubernetes; persistent DB (Postgres + optional vector DB for similarity).


# API

- stateless REST.
- API-driven so different UI versions (web / mobile / third-party) can consume the same backend.
- OpenAPI format planned (once server logic is finalized).
- API key per user + per instance (Phase 2+).
- Rate limits configurable via admin config (no UI needed):
  - default: 5 Thesis creations per min per user (Phase 2+).
  - applies to all write operations (Thesis + Arguments).
- Reading is free. Bot protection to be added later.
- Editing requires the caller to be the author (checked server-side via `user_id`).
- Archiving requires admin (in MVP: everyone is admin).


# Current API endpoints (MVP)

## Theses
- `GET  /api/theses` (query: `trending=true` | `top=true` | `limit=N`) - list.
- `POST /api/theses` (body: `{ title, description, categories, author_id?, location? }`) - create.
- `GET  /api/theses/[id]` - single thesis + vote_summary.
- `PUT  /api/theses/[id]` (body: `{ title?, description?, categories?, user_id }`) - update (author only).
- `DELETE /api/theses/[id]` - hard delete (admin, rarely used - prefer archive).
- `POST /api/theses/[id]/archive` (body: `{ archived: boolean }`) - archive/unarchive.
- `POST /api/theses/[id]/vote` (body: `{ user_id, type }`) - toggle vote.

## Arguments
- `GET  /api/arguments?thesis_id=X` - list arguments for a thesis.
- `POST /api/arguments` (body: `{ thesis_id, content, attributes, stance, forked_from_id?, author_id? }`) - create.
- `GET  /api/arguments/[id]` - single argument.
- `PUT  /api/arguments/[id]` (body: `{ content?, attributes?, user_id }`) - update (author only).
- `DELETE /api/arguments/[id]` - hard delete.
- `POST /api/arguments/[id]/vote` (body: `{ user_id, type }`) - toggle vote.

## Stats
- `GET /api/stats` - returns `{ heat: {thesisId: ratio}, arguments: {thesisId: count} }`.
- `GET /api/activity?thesis_id=?` - returns `ActivityDay[]` for last 84 days (platform-wide or per thesis).


# Server-side logic still to build

For the upcoming server discussion:
- Persistent storage layer (currently: in-memory Map, lost on restart).
- Rate limiting middleware.
- Anonymous identity + magic-link auth.
- Author enforcement for edit endpoints (currently: client sends user_id, server trusts it - naive for MVP).
- Similarity clustering (local LLM + vector search).
- Event log for changelog / snapshots.
- Bot protection / abuse detection.


# RBAC

## Roles
- `user`: default. Can create, vote, edit own.
- `qualified user`: trusted (vouched by others). Vote weight can be higher (future).
- `moderator`: can archive Theses, mark abusive users.
- `admin`: can delete users, manage categories, adjust rate limits.

MVP: everyone is admin (no auth).


# Login (Phase 2+)

- UUID-based identity (anonymous).
- Magic link for authentication (no email/password clutter).
- SSO for enterprise (cert / OIDC / LDAP).
- Private and school instances: magic link only.
- MVP: no login. Anonymous UUID stored in browser localStorage.
